page.title: 13SEWAGE WORKS
page.content: The{sewage works}are looked after by the{Council.}The{sewage}which comes from the near by town of{Guisbrough, runs down a pipe, gets cleaned, before it runs down to the{sea}off the coast of{Redcar.}There was a clean{stream which we crossed. On the other side there was a field of wheat.We passed 2 farms{Woodhouse Farm}and{Park Farm. There was{wheat, barley and oil seed {rape}growing in the fields. Going up towards{Park Wood}we saw a{dismantled {railway.}You could tell it was dismantled because there were tracks, then grass in the middle. We walked up into the{woodland}which was{mixed coniferous and deciduos. Amongst the undergrowth there were many{wild {flowers}eg.{Wood Sorrel , Bluebell , {Celandine, Comfree and Wood Anemone.
